    <section class="section">
      <h2>Current Status</h2>
      <p>As of May 2026, the Korean stock auto-trading program is in live-account operation. The latest work improved issues found over the weekend and adjusted the structure for a seed expansion toward roughly ₩10M.</p>
      <p>This update is not the first operations record for the program. It reflects the first trading day after applying the updated auto-trading logic from the weekend upgrade.</p>
      <p><strong>Core of this update</strong></p>
      <ul class="gains-list">
        <li>Automatically recalculate per-position budget based on total assets</li>
        <li>Limit maximum weight per position</li>
        <li>Evaluate high-priced stocks by total-asset ratio</li>
        <li>Keep RS / MA20 deviation / stop-loss / holding-period conditions unchanged</li>
        <li>Do not create exceptions for specific stocks</li>
      </ul>
      <p>After adding ₩5M, total assets expanded toward roughly ₩10M. This makes high-priced blue-chip stocks structurally evaluable inside the portfolio from a price standpoint. But the buy conditions were not relaxed. Stocks that fail the conditions remain blocked.</p>
      <p><strong>First trading day after the update</strong></p>
      <ul class="gains-list">
        <li>LG Electronics trailing sell executed normally</li>
        <li>Realized P&L: +₩12,000</li>
        <li>New buys: 0 — no stocks passed the RS criteria</li>
        <li>Shinhan Financial waiting for holding-period sell</li>
        <li>SK Hynix became structurally more feasible after the high-priced stock improvement, but buy was blocked by the MA20 deviation condition</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Zero new buys was not an error. It was the cash-holding principle working as intended when there were no strong candidates. Under the ₩5M structure, high-priced stocks were structurally difficult to buy. Under the ₩10M structure, they can be bought, but only when the conditions are met.</p>
      <p><strong>Next actions</strong></p>
      <ul class="gains-list">
        <li>Confirm the Shinhan Financial holding-period sell result</li>
        <li>Validate the early-sell branch for positions exceeding the holding period</li>
        <li>Review classification improvements for BUY / RS pass / final buy in scan_log.json</li>
        <li>Reconsider the RS exemption policy for additional buys</li>
        <li>Write the first-week operations report under the ₩10M seed structure</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="timeline-cta"><a href="/en/log/2026-05-04-auto-trading-weekend-upgrade-first-trading-day/">First Trading Day After Weekend Upgrade Log →</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/en/log/2026-05-01-auto-trading-v2-upgrade-plan/">v2.0 Upgrade Log →</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/en/insight/insight-024/">Insight →</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>The Problem Being Solved</h2>
      <p>Can a non-coder build and operate a real automated trading system by collaborating with AI?</p>
      <p>The operator handles <strong>judgment</strong>. AI handles <strong>execution</strong>. The question is whether this division of roles holds up when real capital is on the line. The current ₩10M-level structure is the answer in progress.</p>
      <p>The goal is not profit. The goal is the experience of building a system where AI operates real capital — by hand, from scratch.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Structure and How It Works</h2>
      <p>Three roles. The operator (철부지) sets strategy direction and makes final calls. GPT (메타철부지) handles strategy design and research. Claude Code handles code analysis and modification. KIS API (Korea Investment Securities) executes orders on the live account.</p>
      <p>Buy decisions run through a rule engine. RSI, MA20 deviation, market regime (5-condition scoring), RS filter — candidates that pass all four conditions are sorted by strength and scanned 3 times per day (10:00 / 13:00 / 14:00). Sells are handled automatically: +6% take-profit or trailing stop (+4% activation / -2% from peak), -3% stop-loss.</p>
    </section>

